# Use the Makefile for project commands

This repo’s workflows are wired in the root **Makefile**. Prefer those targets so installs, checks, and tests stay consistent.

## Frontend (SvelteKit in `frontend/`)

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install deps | `make frontend-install` |
| Tests only | `make frontend-test` |
| Typecheck + lint + tests | `make frontend-check` |
| Production build | `make frontend-build` |
| Dev server | `make frontend-run` |

Do **not** default to `cd frontend && npm test` (or similar) when verifying the frontend; use **`make frontend-test`** unless the user asks otherwise.

## Backend (`backend/`)

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install | `make backend-install` |
| Tests | `make backend-test` |
| Lint + types + tests | `make backend-check` |
| API dev server | `make backend-run` |

## Whole repo

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install everything | `make install` |
| All tests | `make test` |
| All checks | `make check` |

When suggesting verification after changes, cite the matching **`make …`** target.
